mobiles.name: hydra seahydra
mobiles.long_description: A multiheaded sea hydra is here.
mobiles.description:
It's bloody huge! And whats worse, it's got lots of heads and they are
all glaring angrily at you!

mobiles.name: gatekeeper gate keeper
mobiles.description:
The gate keeper glares at you, you better have some money as he cannot
abide timewasters!

mobiles.name: Troll Guard
mobiles.long_description: A troll stands here, on guard.
mobiles.description: A troll guard is here, and he doesn't look very happy to see you.

objects.name: gate key
objects.description: A gate key has been left here.

extra_descr_data.description: The gate key opens the way to the new world.

objects.name: scroll riddle
objects.description: A scroll has carelessly been left here.

extra_descr_data.description:
The scroll has a strange phrase drawn upon it.

'Those Who Must Be Kept'

objects.name: dragonquest666
objects.description: A White Dragonstone lies here gleaming.

rooms.name: The open sea
rooms.description:
As you look around, all you can see is open sea all around you.
Thankfully you still have your bearings, so you know where you are,
but you just pray that you are never lost here. For such an expanse
of sea with no land marks can be treacherous to those who are lost.

rooms.name: A savage storm
rooms.description:
The wind whips up, and the seas turn dark and choppy. The waves
increase in size and you become disorientated. You get tossed about
and have no idea which way north is. You are lost, and you can but
hope you survive the storm.

rooms.name: The doldrums
rooms.description:
You are becalmed! Everywhere you look the sea is a mirror. Not a
breath of wind is felt. You slowly drift with no idea of direction.
Much more of this and you'll go mad. Lost and drifting, with no
sense of direction. How cruel the sea can be.

rooms.name: The sea mist
rooms.description:
The sea mist envelops you and sends your compass haywire. There
are no stars to navigate by and no compass readings. You are lost
and your only company is the blanket of whiteness which is the fog.
You occasionally hear noises coing from the fog. And you occasionally
glimps movement within the fog, shapeless shadows fleeting just out
of you line of sight.

rooms.name: The whirlpool
rooms.description:
You are sucked into a whirlpool. As you cirlce the main vortex you
spin wildly and rapidly, making you very dizzy and sick. You very
quickly lose all sense of direction as you try and escape the
inevitable.

rooms.name: The sea mist
rooms.description:
The sea mist envelops you and sends your compass haywire. There
are no stars to navigate by and no compass readings. You are lost
and your only company is the blanket of whiteness which is the fog.
You occasionally hear noises coing from the fog. And you occasionally
glimps movement within the fog, shapeless shadows fleeting just out
of you line of sight.

rooms.name: The open sea
rooms.description:
As you look around, all you can see is open sea all around you. 
Thankfully you still have your bearings, so you know where you are, 
but you just pray that you are never lost here. For such an expanse
of sea with no land marks can be treacherous to those who are lost.

rooms.description:
You are in the infamous Bermuda Triangle, where there is no direction 
and people who enter it hardly ever leave it..... well not alive 
anyway! Better be careful and try and find a way out.

rooms.name: A volcanic beach
rooms.description:
You find yourself on a beach, a strange black beach. You realise 
that the reason for this is probably the giant volcano that occupies 
practically the whole island. You just hope that it's dormant.

rooms.name: On the slopes of the volcano
rooms.description:
You are halfway up the side of the volcano, as you look around you 
have a magnificent view of the blue sea and the black beach 
stretching around the island. Still, not at the top yet though.

rooms.name: The summit of the volcano
rooms.description:
You have reached the summit of the volcano. As you look into the crater
you can see several holes that appear to lead down into the depths of
the volcano. As you examine these you find one with the initials JKR
carved into the side. So, someone has been here before you. Determined,
you decide that if you are going to enter, it will be down this cave.

rooms.name: Inside the first cave
rooms.description:
This is the first cave into the volcano. Here you can see the
initials JKR scratched into the side of one of the walls. So at
least you know someone has been here before you. Still, who knows
how far he got? You look around and you do not see much. Just
darkness as the tunnel runs deeper into the volcano.

rooms.name: Inside the volcano
rooms.description:
You find yourself in a tunnel deep within the volcano. It's pretty
dark in here.And it seems almost too quiet, and noone iit going to hear 
you from deep within a volcano. All the tunnels appear to be the same, 
if only there was some way to tell them apart. 
Still, no point in hanging around, best press on.

rooms.name: Inside the volcano
rooms.description:
Another dark tunnel, sounds echo back and forth but you cannot make
any sense of them. Maybe it's just your own movement causing the
strange effect, or maybe not. Who know what lives down here? You just
hope you don't run into any!

You are now just outside Midgaard, as you look back you can see
the city gates. Also you see the grate that normally stops people
from just wandering in on the river. The river seems to extend
westwards, but all you can tell is that is disappears into the
dreaded Haon-Dor forest. But at least you will have the current
with you, should you decide to carry on downstream.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
You are now well into the Haon-Dor forest, the trees overhang the
river most of the way down. Almost totally blocking out the sun.
The only noises are of wild creatures within the forest and the
occasional bump as a root of a tree bangs the underside of the boat.
At least, you hope it's a root!

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
You are approaching the heart of the Haon-Dor wood, and now a 
strange kind of silence has fallen around you. No noise can
penetrate the forest this deep. And any cries from help from you
would never reach even the edge of the forest. For this area is
cursed and most people never survive to tell of their passage
through it. Be careful.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
Phew, made it! Still, there is a long way to go yet. Best not 
hang around here too long, just get out of this cursed wood while
you still can!

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
You find yourself at the entrance to the swamps. This is the lowland of the
river where the river has silted up making the water very murky and very
smelly. Best move of, the smell is appauling.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
The river continues towards the west. But you are now deep within a
rather smelly swap. The water is more solid than a liquid. You just
begin to wonder whjat could possibly live here! As you look around
you can see a track leading from the waters edge into the swamp.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
You are still stuck in this reeking swamp, further to the west you
can see a fork in the river. In the far distance to the west you
catch a glimps of a deep blue sea.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
You find yourself at a fork in the river. One north and one south. You
wonder what they could lead to ..... or maybe you should just forget it 
and carry on westwards, towards the sea and fresh air.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
To the north you can see a rather large forboding tower, but it's
twin is to the south of you. They almost seem to be guarding this
inlet from something from the west. Or maybe they are here to keep
you from going west?

rooms.name: Mouth of the river
rooms.description:
You are at the mouth of the river, away from the delta swamp and breathing
in fresh air again! The open sea lies to your west, or the way back home
lays to the east. Still you cannot decide the exact reason for the two 
towers, yet they seem strangly empty. Who knows, someday someone will
fill them again.....what a frightening thought!

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
You are north of the fork, and you see a huge tower to the west. 
You wonder what reason such a structure could be built.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
Still in the stinking swamp, and that tower just seems too strange for
words.

rooms.name: Bend in the river
rooms.description:
The river bends towards the west, heading back to the sea. And yet, it
takes you closer to the landing pier of the northern tower.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
You can see the sea to the west, and a landing pier for the tower 
just before that.

rooms.name: Mouth of the river
rooms.description:
You are at the northern mouth of the river. There is a pier here 
that leads to land to the south.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
To the north you see a fork in the river. The river also carries on to
the south.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
To the south you see a bend in the river. To the west is the dark south
tower. Far to the north is a fork in the river.

rooms.name: Bend in the river
rooms.description:
You are at a bend in the river. Far to the north is a fork in the river
and the norther tower. To the west is a landing pier and open sea.

rooms.name: On the river
rooms.description:
To the east is a bend in the river. To the west is a badly kept landing
pier and beyond that the open sea. To the south is a large rock outcropping.

rooms.name: Mouth of the river
rooms.description:
There is a landing pier here that leads to the north. And to the west 
the open sea. Further to the north you see a large castle.

rooms.name: The beach
rooms.description:
You find yourself on a golden beach that stretches for miles
both north and south. You are just relieved to get away from the
sea. This seems a safe spot to rest, until you are ready to
carry on with your travels.

rooms.name: Joker's little get-away
rooms.description:
This is Jokers spare room, kinda his secret getaway...leave those
Deities and thier problems behind...just GO AWAY!

rooms.name: Jokers Room
rooms.description:
This is Jokers room, visitors are not welcome.
The room is full of electrical equipment, and Large bed and a large
wardrobe. In the corner is a huge jukebox, full of his favourite CD's
you name it, it is there.

rooms.name: Avalons Room
rooms.description: Avalon needs to send Valis a desc :>
